# Sindireceita backup recipient (age v1, X25519).
#
# ============================================================================
# THIS FILE IS A NON-FUNCTIONAL BOOTSTRAP PLACEHOLDER.
#
# `backup.sh` will fail hard at `age -R` until this file is rotated. That is
# intentional: it forces the operator to generate the production keypair on
# the backup host (where the private half belongs) BEFORE any real PII is
# encrypted to a recipient whose private half might still exist outside the
# backup host's trust boundary.
#
# To install:
#   1. Run `scripts/generate-backup-key.sh` on the backup host. It writes
#      the private key to /etc/sindireceita/age-backup.key with mode 0440
#      and ownership root:sindireceita-backup, and prints the matching
#      public key on stdout.
#   2. Replace the marker line at the bottom of this file with that public
#      key. Keep the comment header.
#   3. SOPS-encrypt the private key into infra/sops/age-backup.key.enc per
#      docs/operations/backup-restore.md § "Primeira instalação".
#   4. Stash a second copy of the cleartext private key in the offline
#      cofre — see § "Cofre offline".
#
# Why a placeholder and not a "real" bootstrap key? See SIN-62220 must-fix #2
# and the SIN-62250 security review: a real bootstrap keypair generated in
# the dev workspace risks its private half lingering in /tmp on the heartbeat
# host that produced it. A placeholder eliminates that vector by making
# rotation a hard requirement, not a discipline check.
#
# Rotation procedure (after the first install): see docs/operations/backup-restore.md
# § "Rotacao de chave".
# ============================================================================

age1placeholder0000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000
